the dillards department stores chain contents  early life  career  personal life and death  references early lifeedit william t dillard was born on september   to thomas j dillard and hattie mae gibson dillard both grocers dillard found employment with sears  roebuck company where he gained experience in retail business he graduated from the university of arkansas with a degree in business administration and earned a masters degree from columbia university he was a member of the lambda chi alpha fraternity careeredit dillard returned to arkansas and opened his first retail store in  in the town of nashville arkansas after he borrowed us from his father to sign the lease and install shelves and stocking those shelves with merchandise supplied on generous credit extended on the basis of wholesalers long dealings with his father in  he sold his nashville store and opened stores in texas followed by more stores across the southern united states in  he opened his first store in a mall in austin texas and foreshadowed the boom of malls in  he opened more stores in malls in little rock arkansas and tulsa oklahoma he used computerized checkouts to track inventory by the turn of the century dillards department stores was the third largest department store chain in the united states he retired in  his eldest son william t dillard ii took over as ceo and his second son alex dillard as president his daughter drue corbusier and denise mahaffy and a third son mike dillard serve as vice presidents personal life and deathedit dillard married alexa latimer on june   and they had five children he was an episcopalian and a republican he died at his home in little rock on february   at the age of  from heart failure referencesedit  a b c d e f g h nndb  a b c d e f g h encyclopedia of arkansas  a b c d e f g h i leslie kaufman william t dillard founder of a retail chain dies at  the new york times february   authority control worldcat identities viaf  lccn n isni     gnd x retrieved fr