 malls in  he opened more stores in malls in little rock arkansas and tulsa oklahoma he used computerized checkouts to track inventory by the turn of the century dillards department stores was the third largest department store chain in the united states he retired in  his eldest son william t dillard ii took over as ceo and his second son alex dillard as president his daughter drue corbusier and denise mahaffy and a third son mike dillard serve as vice presidents personal life and deathedit dillard married alexa latimer on june   and they had five children he was an episcopalian and a republican he died at his home in little rock on february   at the age of  from heart failure referencesedit  a b c d e f g h nndb  a b c d e f g h encyclopedia of arkansas  a b c d e f g h i leslie kaufman william t dillard founder of a retail chain dies at  the new york times february   authority control worldcat identities viaf  lccn n isni     gnd x retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlewilliamtdillardoldid categories  births deathspeople from howard county arkansasuniversity of arkansas alumnicolumbia university alumniamerican businesspeople in retailingamerican episcopaliansthcentury american businesspeoplebusinesspeople from arkansashidden categories pages using infobox person with unknown parametersinfobox person using religionarticles with hcardswikipedia articles with viaf identifierswikipedia articles with lccn identifierswikipedia articles with isni identifierswikipedia articles with gnd identifiers navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport creat